The paper deals with approximation algorithms for two combinatorial optimization problems, namely the Densest k-Subhypergraph Problem and the Set Union Knapsack Problem. These problems are typically studied in the areas of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), and game theory (cs.GT).
